s dynamics. The course of the seasons and weekly and daily rhythms of discharge, temperature, work and other patterns make the river dwellers' world an ever-transforming phenomenon. The flows of life and the frictions of everyday encounters continually remake the river and its inhabitants, negotiating national strategies, economic power, people's ingenuity, and the currents of the Kemi River.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEthnologyzFinlandzKemi River. 4aCultural Anthropology. 4aCultural Geography. 4aEcology. 4aEnvironmental History. 4aFishing. 4aHydropower. 4aLapland. 4aNature. 4aSeasons. 4aSociety. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aCultural Anthropology.  aCultural Geography.  aEcology.  aEnvironmental History.  aFishing.  aHydropower.  aLapland.  aNature.  aSeasons.  aSociety.1 aLiebig, Oliver D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishz978311131910008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2023z9783111318141oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2023z9783111024950oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839467374?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839467374423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839467374/original  a978-3-11-131910-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Eng